  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Checking Project Structure**\n\nOkay, so I see that `index.css` is basically just importing Tailwind. I am double-checking the project files now, to be thorough. It looks like the file tree is pretty bare, but I am still processing the available information. I will get back with further updates shortly.\n\n\n**Analyzing HTML and Design**\n\nI\'m now diving into `/index.html` to review font loading and ensure we align with design guidelines. Reactive rules emphasize importing fonts into `src/index.css`. The cafe, Deyar, is inspired by Himachali nature and folklore, with the Himalayan bear as a central visual element. Color palette includes rust, cocoa, dark coffee brown, and a warm cream background which I am making our primary background color!\n\n\n**Defining Page Structure**\n\nOkay, I\'m solidifying the page outlines now. I\'ve got a homepage with a hero section, and menu, about us, contact pages, and a reservation system. The menu\'s getting an interactive ordering system, while the contact page will show live open/closed status. I\'m also planning a customer testimonial carousel as an extra.\n\n\n**Planning Component Structure**\n\nI am expanding the planned component layout. I\'ll include seasonal special highlights and a newsletter signup with a success message. I\'ll organize types in `/src/types.ts`, and data like menu items in `/src/data.ts`. I\'m starting on the following React components: `/src/components/Navbar.tsx`, `/src/components/Hero.tsx`, `/src/components/Menu.tsx`, and `/src/components/About.tsx`.\n\n\n**Expanding Component Array**\n\nI\'m now outlining additional React components: `/src/components/Contact.tsx` for operational hours, an interactive map, and a contact form with success triggers. I\'m also planning `/src/components/Reservations.tsx` for the table reservation engine. I\'ve got `/src/components/CartDrawer.tsx`, a slide-out cart overlay with size options, milk options, sugar levels, price calculations, and checkout animation with a progress tracker. Additionally, I\'ll be creating `/src/components/Specials.tsx` for the seasonal specials slider, and `/src/components/Footer.tsx` for a clean footer with an email signup. The design philosophy is \"Mood First\".\n\nI am changing fonts to reflect design choices. I will use \'Playfair Display\' for the display fonts and pair it with \'Inter\' for clean text, and \'Outfit\' or \'Space Grotesk\' for modern cozy headers. I will import \'Playfair Display\' and \'Outfit\' in `src/index.css`.\n\n\n**Verifying Font and Color Scheme**\n\nI\'ve confirmed the font rules in `src/index.css`, which are great. I\'m checking color definitions now. I\'m adding brand colors: a warm, rich cream for the background, a lighter cream for accents, and a rust/ochre-brown. I will define these in the theme section of the CSS file for easier custom utility classes.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view the `vite.config.ts` file to see the Vite plugin and development configuration."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 139662751
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
