  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Success & Refinement**\n\nFantastic! I\'ve confirmed successful compilation and app build. My next thought is double-checking for any other potential file clean-up needs, now that the user\'s initial request has been achieved. The outcome looks beautiful.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have created a responsive, editorial caf\303\251 website for **Deyar**, rooted in Himachali storytelling, Deodar conifer pine forests, and the folklore of the Himalayan bear. \n\nAll primary branding, layouts, colors, and functionalities from your design directives are implemented using **React 18**, **TypeScript**, and **Tailwind CSS**.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Editorial Identity\n*   **The Himalayan Hearth Palette**: Utilizes the brand guidelines with a warm, rich cream backdrop (`#FDFCE9`), Rust/Ochre (`#9C522F`) titles, cocoa accents (`#845D4B`), and a dark espresso coffee tone (`#4B2F1B`) for text structures.\n*   **Aesthetic Typography**: Paired **Playfair Display** (a serif font representing oral mountain history) alongside **Outfit** (for headings and titles) and highly legible **Inter** for descriptions.\n*   **Deyar Brand Mark Seal**: Designed a custom vector SVG centerpiece depicting the legendary Himalayan bear tilted upward, balancing a golden pinecone on its nose as mountains and stars glow behind it.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\227\272\357\270\217 Seamless Page Blueprint & Modules\n\n#### 1. Home tab (Heritage Splash)\n*   An animated hero showcasing the rotating **Deyar Brand Seal**, a folklore tagline, and prompt triggers to the *Menu* or *Reservations*.\n*   **Oral Lore Section**: Chronicles the story of the Himalayan Bear guardian and his playful pinecone. Includes a rustic, framed wilderness photograph.\n*   **Limited-Time Seasonal Specials**: An interactive slider spotlighting local forest ingredients (e.g., *Pinecone-Sage Brew* or *Himachali Spiced Latte*).\n\n#### 2. Kitchen Menu (Interactive Catalog)\n*   **Categorized Grid Filter**: Effortlessly toggles between *All items*, *Coffee Crafts*, *Valley Infusions*, *Hearth Pastries*, and *Seasonal Rotations*. Includes an instant, non-blocking keyword search bar.\n*   **Premium Customization Modal**: Clicking details slides open modifications (e.g., swapping to *Oat Milk (+ $0.75)*, sizing, or dial-in sweetness) with write-in barista notes. Subtotals dynamically recalibrate as adjustments are made.\n\n#### 3. Table Booking (Reservation Wizard)\n1.  **Stage 1 (Credentials)**: Quick-select party size (1\342\200\2238 hikers), a scrollable date picker, and hour arrivals.\n2.  **Stage 2 (Blueprint Map)**: A responsive diagram of the wooden tavern floor. Patrons click on available seating niches (e.g., *Altar Hearth Fireplace Bench*, *Deodar Crest Window Desk*, or semi-outdoor *Forest Skydeck*).\n3.  **Stage 3 (Hiker Info)**: Form inputs capturing names and trail phone contacts.\n4.  **Stage 4 (Printable Stub)**: Generates a beautiful, wood-stamped **Booking Ticket Stub** containing a verification barcode and print layouts.\n\n#### 4. Table/Fireside Diaries (Testimonials)\n*   A stylized dark-mode slide deck highlighting regular hikers\' and travel journalists\' stellar experiences with localized menu items.\n\n#### 5. Hours & Contact (Hiking Coordinates)\n*   **Dynamic Pulse Badge**: Monitors system time and displays an active **\"Deyar Hearth is OPEN now\"** or **\"CLOSED now\"** indicator.\n*   **Visual Topography Hiking Map**: A vector SVG contour map showing real GPS coordinates and hiking directions from the Mall Road Trail Connector, complete with pulsating location markers.\n\n#### 6. Sliding Order Cart Drawer (Full Checkout)\n*   A slide-out panel computing item price modifiers, sales tax, and eco-friendly wood-fiber packaging fees.\n*   Offers choices of **Self Hike-In Pickup** or **Instant Delivery Links** (linking directly to regional partners like *Swiggy* or *Zomato* with custom-painted color badges).\n*   Completing an order loads a status screen featuring an animated steaming coffee extraction timer.\n\n#### 7. Hearth Ledger (Footer)\n*   Houses an elegant **Newsletter Sign-Up Form** on mountain honey migrations and secret fireside dinner gatherings. Correct email input triggers a welcome alert.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 768764239
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
